properties.headline: High Surf Advisory issued February 7 at 4:24PM HST until February 8 at 6:00PM HST by NWS Honolulu HI
properties.description:
...HIGH SURF ADVISORY FOR NORTH AND WEST FACING SHORES OF NIIHAU
KAUAI AND OAHU NORTH FACING SHORES OF MOLOKAI AND MAUI...

.Rough surf will continue through the weekend due to a
combination of strong northerly winds and large seas. A large,
long-period northwest swell is expected to build down the island
chain tonight and peak Saturday, which will support advisory-
level surf continuing along exposed coasts. A brief downward
trend is expected Sunday, when surf heights should drop below
advisory levels.

* WHAT...Surf 8 to 12 feet Saturday.

* WHERE...west facing shores of Oahu.

* WHEN...From midnight tonight to 6 PM HST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Moderate. Large breaking waves and strong currents
will make entering the water dangerous.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
properties.instruction:
Beachgoers, swimmers, and surfers should heed all advice given by
ocean safety officials and exercise caution.

Boaters should expect recreational surfers and body boarders
utilizing harbor channels to access surfing areas.

NWSheadline: HIGH SURF ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 6 PM HST SATURDAY
